{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778904642185,"sessionID":"ses_1d108571bffeBfolSmUz0E2IbX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"functions.read:32","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo","offset":156266,"limit":40},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n156266: id: UBERON:0013540\n156267: name: Brodmann (1909) area 9\n156268: def: \"A cytoarchitecturally defined portion of the frontal cortex in the brain of humans and other primates. It contributes to the dorsolateral and medial prefrontal cortex and plays a role in executive functions such as working memory, planning, inhibition, decision-making, and reasoning. Its cytoarchitecture is referred to as granular due to the concentration of granule cells in layer IV. Its internal pyramidal layer (V) is divisible into two sublayers, an outer layer 5a of densely distributed medium-size ganglion cells that partially merges with layer IV, and an inner, clearer, cell-poor layer 5b; the pyramidal cells of sublayer 3b of the external pyramidal layer (III) are smaller and sparser in distribution; the external granular layer (II) is narrow, with small numbers of sparsely distributed granule cells.\" [Wikipedia:Brodmann_area_9, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4964-5083]\n156269: synonym: \"area 9 of Brodmann\" EXACT [FMA:68606]\n156270: synonym: \"area 9 of Brodmann (guenon)\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1024]\n156271: synonym: \"area 9 of Brodmann-1909\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1740]\n156272: synonym: \"area frontalis granularis\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [BIRNLEX:1740, Wikipedia:Brodmann_area_9]\n156273: synonym: \"B09-9\" BROAD OMO:0003000 [BIRNLEX:1740, NIFSTD:SumsDB_abbrevSource]\n156274: synonym: \"B09-9\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1740]\n156275: synonym: \"BA9\" RELATED [FMA:68606]\n156276: synonym: \"Brodmann (1909) area 9\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1740]\n156277: synonym: \"Brodmann area 9\" EXACT [FMA:68606]\n156278: synonym: \"Brodmann area 9, granular frontal\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1740]\n156279: synonym: \"brodmann's area 9\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1024]\n156280: synonym: \"granular frontal area\" EXACT [FMA:68606]\n156281: property_value: dcterms-date \"2026-05-16T04:09:31Z\" xsd:dateTime\n156282: property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3448\" xsd:anyURI\n156283: relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4964-5083 ! Dana Gabuxda\n156284: xref: BIRNLEX:1740\n156285: xref: FMA:68606\n156286: xref: neuronames:1024 {source=\"BIRNLEX:1740\"}\n156287: xref: UMLS:C1272531 {source=\"BIRNLEX:1740\"}\n156288: xref: Wikipedia:Brodmann_area_9\n156289: is_a: UBERON:0013529 {source=\"NIFSTD\"} ! Brodmann area\n156290: relationship: part_of UBERON:0009834 {source=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3308-6245\"} ! dorsolateral prefrontal cortex\n156291: \n156292: [Term]\n156293: id: UBERON:0013541\n156294: name: Brodmann (1909) area 10\n156295: def: \"Brodmann area 10, or BA10, is part of the frontal cortex in the human brain. BA10 encompasses the most anterior part of the frontal cortex, known as the frontopolar region. This area is believed to play a part in strategic processes involved in memory retrieval and executive function. This area is also called frontopolar area 10, and it refers to a subdivision of the cytoarchitecturally defined frontal region of cerebral cortex. It occupies the most rostral portions of the superior frontal gyrus and the middle frontal gyrus. In humans, on the medial aspect of the hemisphere it is bounded ventrally by the superior rostral sulcus (H). It does not extend as far as the cingulate sulcus. Cytoarchitecturally it is bounded dorsally by the granular frontal area 9, caudally by the middle frontal area 46, and ventrally by the orbital area 47 and by the rostral area 12 or, in an early version of Brodmann's cortical map (Brodmann-1909), the prefrontal Brodmann area 11-1909.\" [Wikipedia:Brodmann_area_10]\n156296: synonym: \"area 10 of Brodmann\" EXACT [FMA:68607]\n156297: synonym: \"area 10 of Brodmann-1909\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1741]\n156298: synonym: \"area frontopolaris\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1741]\n156299: synonym: \"B09-10\" BROAD OMO:0003000 [BIRNLEX:1741, NIFSTD:SumsDB_abbrevSource]\n156300: synonym: \"B09-10\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1741]\n156301: synonym: \"BA10\" RELATED [FMA:68607]\n156302: synonym: \"Brodmann (1909) area 10\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1741]\n156303: synonym: \"Brodmann area 10\" EXACT [FMA:68607]\n156304: synonym: \"Brodmann area 10, frontoplar\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1741]\n156305: synonym: \"lateral orbital area\" EXACT [FMA:68607]\n\n(Showing lines 156266-156305 of 226197. Use offset=156306 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: UBERON:0013540\nname: Brodmann (1909) area 9\ndef: \"A cytoarchitecturally defined portion of the frontal cortex in the brain of humans and other primates. It contributes to the dorsolateral and medial prefrontal cortex and plays a role in executive functions such as working memory, planning, inhibition, decision-making, and reasoning. Its cytoarchitecture is referred to as granular due to the concentration of granule cells in layer IV. Its internal pyramidal layer (V) is divisible into two sublayers, an outer layer 5a of densely distributed medium-size ganglion cells that partially merges with layer IV, and an inner, clearer, cell-poor layer 5b; the pyramidal cells of sublayer 3b of the external pyramidal layer (III) are smaller and sparser in distribution; the external granular layer (II) is narrow, with small numbers of sparsely distributed granule cells.\" [Wikipedia:Brodmann_area_9, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4964-5083]\nsynonym: \"area 9 of Brodmann\" EXACT [FMA:68606]\nsynonym: \"area 9 of Brodmann (guenon)\" RELATED [NeuroNames:1024]\nsynonym: \"area 9 of Brodmann-1909\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1740]\nsynonym: \"area frontalis granularis\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [BIRNLEX:1740, Wikip